TI  - Optimizing IoT communication for enhanced data transmission in smart farming ecosystems
AU  - Osman, Radwa Ahmed
T2  - Expert Systems with Applications
AB  - In the area of smart farming, the integration of Internet of Things (IoT) devices has started a disruptive wave, changing old farming approaches into a smart farming landscape. This evolution is based on the seamless interconnectedness of sensors and technologies, which provides farmers with unprecedented real-time insights into their operations. However, the reliability and quality of data supplied by these IoT devices is a significant barrier. This study focuses on optimizing Agriculture IoT communication in order to improve data transmission efficiency within smart farming ecosystems. This study looks on the optimization of Agriculture IoT communication, with the goal of increasing data transmission efficiency within smart farming ecosystems. The proposed model achieves a balance between energy efficiency and data throughput by strategically applying Lagrange optimization techniques and Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNN), all while addressing critical smart farming parameters such as temperature, humidity, soil moisture and animal health. The rigorous assessment of the ideal IoT sensors transmission power inside the smart farm infrastructure is at the heart of this effort. This study combines mathematical optimization with cutting-edge deep learning approaches to highlight the critical relevance of reliable data in ensuring crop health and vitality. By strengthening communication networks, this technique lays the framework for powerful smart farm ecosystems capable of rapidly adapting to dynamic environmental perturbations, ultimately increasing crop productivity, animal health, and global sustainability.
