TI  - State-of-the-art in real-time virtual interfaces for tractors and farm machines: A systematic review
AU  - Lohan, Shiv Kumar
AU  - Prakash, Chander
AU  - Lohan, Navjeet
AU  - Kansal, Sachin
AU  - Karkee, Manoj
T2  - Computers and Electronics in Agriculture
AB  - This systematic literature review (SLR) investigates the role of Virtual Reality (VR) and Augmented Reality (AR) technologies in enhancing agricultural practices, specifically focusing on their applications in tractors and other farm machinery. As agriculture increasingly shifts toward mechanization and precision farming, the need for effective operator training, improved safety measures, and ergonomic design has become paramount where VR and AR-based modeling and simulation play vital roles. A comprehensive literature search represents 122 relevant studies published in 88 journals/ proceedings between 2000 and 2023, drawing contributions from 421 authors across 211 organizations from 36 countries. The review utilized established databases, including Scopus, Web of Science, and Dimensions, and employed the PRISMA framework for systematic analysis. The results revealed that VR and AR technologies significantly enhance operator training, improve real-time monitoring, and facilitate informed decision-making in agricultural operations. Significant advancements were observed in countries such as the United States, China, and Italy, highlighting a growing global interest in utilizing these technologies in enhancing agriculture machinery development and adoption. Key results indicate that while VR and AR applications improve efficiency and safety, challenges remain, including high costs, sensor integration complexities, and scalability issues, and communicational latency. This SLR presents valuable insights into the current state of knowledge and technology regarding VR and AR in agriculture, serving as a foundation for future research aimed at overcoming existing barriers and maximizing the potential of these technologies to revolutionize agricultural practices and promote sustainability in the sector.
