TI  - Applications and prospects of photoplethysmography technology in animal husbandry: A comprehensive review
AU  - Song, DY
AU  - Zou, FL
AU  - Wang, LJ
AU  - Wang, HY
T2  - COMPUTERS AND ELECTRONICS IN AGRICULTURE
AB  - The increasing demand for sustainable and ethically managed livestock production has intensified the need for precise and continuous health and welfare monitoring. Photoplethysmography (PPG), a non-invasive and lowcost optical technique, shows strong potential for capturing key physiological signals related to stress, disease, and reproduction in animals. This review systematically examines the current progress of PPG in livestock farming, beginning with its principles and technical classifications, and evaluating its feasibility for use on animal body surfaces. It then explores practical applications in physiological monitoring, welfare assessment, and reproductive management. Finally, the review highlights major technical challenges and discusses emerging strategies to support the effective implementation of PPG in precision livestock systems. By integrating recent advances, this review provides a foundation for future research and facilitates the translation of PPG into practical tools for smart animal farming.
